modules.description: Provides functions to read from and write to a mutable byte array, with support for dynamic resizing of the underlying storage. Operates on a fixed-size block structure that can be expanded as needed. Used to simulate disk-like behavior in memory for testing or temporary data storage.

Provides functions to manage an in-memory block device, including reading from and writing to sectors, resizing, connecting, and disconnecting. Operates on types like `int64`, `Cstruct.t list`, and custom error types for I/O operations. Used to create and manipulate a temporary storage layer for testing or high-speed access.
